This page documents published academic research about Emacs. All disciplines are relevant, in lexical order by the first author, across all disciplines.

There is also a Zotero group called [https://www.zotero.org/groups/2392126/emacs/ Emacs].

Thanks to contributors on [https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/djrlib/academic_research_about_emacs/ /r/emacs] and [https://emacs.stackexchange.com/questions/53236/academic-research-about-emacs Emacs StackExchange site].

Palmer, J.; Duffy, T.; Gomoll, K; Gomoll, T.; Richards-Palmquist. J. and Trumble, J. A. 1988. [https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/abstract/document/6920/references The design and evaluation of online help for Unix EMACS: capturing the user in menu design], in /IEEE Transactions on Professional Communication/, vol. 31, no. 1, pp. 44-51, March 1988. doi:10.1109/47.6920.

Twidale, Michael B.; Jones, M. Cameron. 2005. [https://www.ideals.illinois.edu/handle/2142/9607 "Let them use emacs": the interaction of simplicity and appropriation]. /International reports on socio-informatics/ 2(2) 66-71.

Stallman, R. M. (1981). [https://doi.org/10.1145/800209.806466 EMACS the Extensible, Customizable Self-documenting Display Editor]. /Proceedings of the ACM SIGPLAN SIGOA Symposium on Text Manipulation/, 147–156.

Zhong, Shudan and Xu, Hong. 2019. [https://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?doid=3301275.3302272 Intelligently recommending key bindings on physical keyboards with demonstrations in Emacs]. In /Proceedings of the 24th International Conference on Intelligent User Interfaces/ (IUI), 12–17. doi:10.1145/3301275.3302272.

Guy Lapalme.  1998.  [https://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/ab48/0568f9a0e4a6fc3b25918c1a481bb1b99c37.pdf Dynamic Tabbing for Automatic Indentation with the Layout Rule].  Journal of Functional Programming, 8(5), pp493-502.
